JO  - AMJ
SP  - 148
EP  - 163
VL  - 24
IS  - 1
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Absenteeism and performance indices accounted for substantial variance in bank teller voluntary turnover (resignation) and involuntary turnover (dismissal). Predictor and criteria relationships changed substantially for individuals newly employed in 1977-78 compared to 1970-76; however, reasonable cross-validation was exhibited. The results suggest a need to include more criterion variables in theoretical models.
AB  - Absenteeism and performance indices accounted for substantial variance in bank teller voluntary turnover (resignation) and involuntary turnover (dismissal). Predictor and criteria relationships changed substantially for individuals newly employed in 1977-78 compared to 1970-76; however, reasonable cross-validation was exhibited. The results suggest a need to include more criterion variables in theoretical models.
